  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.8.4-stable-2423ae01\r\nOS & Version: Linux (Ubuntu 16.04)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nRPC accepting connections that are made via hostname.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nRPC doesn't accept any connections that are made trough a hostname.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nI'm using this command:\r\n\r\n`command=/usr/bin/geth --fast --rpc --rpcaddr 0.0.0.0 --rpcport 8545 --rpccorsdomain * --rpcapi admin,db,eth,debug,net,txpool,personal,web3`\r\n\r\n\r\nIf I try to connect via direct IP address, everything works just fine. If I try to use a hostname that is pointed directly to the IP address, it simply doesn't work, even though any other application works just fine. On web3js, it shows this error:\r\n\r\n> Failed to load: Response to preflight request doesn't pass access control check: No 'Access-Control-Allow-Origin' header is present on the requested resource. Origin 'https://example.com' is therefore not allowed access. The response had HTTP status code 403.\r\n\r\n",
